==Overview== The Musa Ōtsuka Kofun is an {{nihongo|''{{ill|Round Kofun|lt=enpun|ja|円墳|1=Round Kofun|1=Round Kofun|qq=draft}}''|円墳|1=Round Kofun||}}-style circular tumulus with a diameter of 40 meters and a height of 10 meters, and a huge tunnel-style stone [[burial chamber]] with a total length of 18 meters with the opening orientated to the east. It is situated at a strategic location where the ancient route of the [[San'yōdō]] highway crosses the [[Asahi River]]. The burial chamber is made of megalithic blocks of [[granite]] and contains a hollowed-out house-shaped [[sarcophagus]] measuring 2.88 meters long, 1.6 meters wide, and 1.5 meters high. The sarcophagus is made of shell limestone quarried at Mount Namigata in [[Ibara, Okayama]]. The sarcophagus has a hole, from which its [[grave goods]] were robbed in antiquity. It is estimated that the tumulus was built at the end of the 6th century from the shape of the sarcophagus, and it is speculated that this was a mausoleum of the Kibi no Kamimichi clan, a powerful ruling family in ancient [[Kingdom of Kibi]]. <ref name="Shiseki">{{cite book |last1=Isomura |first1=Yukio |last2=Sakai |first2=Hideya |title=(国指定史跡事典) National Historic Site Encyclopedia |date=2012 |publisher=学生社 |isbn=4311750404}}{{in lang|ja}}</ref>
